<subSubSection lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1872,2018]" lastBlockId="43.[151,1436,152,258]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1952,1978]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi, 2010" authorityName="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi" authorityYear="2010" box="[461,655,1953,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteosuturalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[461,655,1953,1978]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">E. luteosuturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[664,759,1952,1978]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but the basal yellow spots on elytra are distinctly larger. Tergite 8 elongated, much longer than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi, 2010" authorityName="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi" authorityYear="2010" box="[632,825,1993,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteosuturalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[632,825,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">E. luteosuturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[832,925,1992,2018]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and parameroids of penis distinctly shorter than pala (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi, 2010" authorityName="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi" authorityYear="2010" box="[303,495,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteosuturalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[303,495,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">E. luteosuturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[503,593,152,178]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
– as long as pala). It may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi, 2010" authorityName="Ruta &amp; Yoshitomi" authorityYear="2010" box="[1157,1261,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Exochomoscirtes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1157,1261,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">E. jaechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1268,1357,152,178]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
on the basis of the more contrasting dorsal pattern and morphology of sternite 9, which is wider in apical portion and tergite 8 with longer parameres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
